<TITLE> Thimpu to host display of Bangladesh goods </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 18 (bdnews24.com) Bhutan will host a Bangladeshi trade fair next month, and both nations are set to sign a trade deal by May, the commerce minister said Wednesday. "Bangladesh has great opportunities to expand trade in Bhutan," Faruq Khan told reporters after a meeting with outgoing Bhutanese ambassador Tshering Dorji. A trade fair showcasing Bangladeshi products will also be held in Bhutan by mid March, the minister said. "Preparations are on to sign the deal and organise the fair." World Bank country director Xian Zhu also met the trade minister Wednesday. bdnews
